cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.SE

This paper primarily deals with security issues in Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), specifically related to the parameters of the network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the impact of the attack on the accuracy of the network, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper proposes a new attack methodology, which could also place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category.
